FRAME magazine (capitalized by its creators; the E in FRAME often appears mirror-reversed on the magazine's cover) is a magazine devoted to interior design, architecture, product design and exhibition design based in Amsterdam, Netherlands. The magazine was first published in 1997 by Frame Publishers and have about 6 issues a year.

Frame magazine is one of the leading interior design publications. Since its launch in 1997, the magazine has remained faithful to its mission: putting interior architecture on the map as a creative profession thatÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s equally important as design and architecture. The magazine is sold in 77 countries and is printed in English, Chinese, Korean and Turkish.

The magazine is published by the parent company 'FRAME Publishers', which also produces various design related books and occasional monographs on the work of prominent companies and people in the design world.[1]
